<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Enliterator</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <%= csp_meta_tag %>

  <%= yield :head %>

  <%# All styling is inline below so the UI works under ANY host asset pipeline
      (Sprockets, Propshaft, or none) without the host needing to precompile an
      engine stylesheet. Do NOT add stylesheet_link_tag here — a Sprockets host
      raises AssetNotPrecompiledError for an engine asset it didn't declare. %>
  <style>
    /* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       ENLITERATOR — SHARED COMPONENT SYSTEM
       ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       This block is the single source of truth for the engine's look. It is
       100% self-contained (no external CSS/JS, no web fonts, no gem) so the UI
       renders under any host pipeline (Sprockets, Propshaft, or none). Do NOT
       add stylesheet_link_tag — a Sprockets host raises AssetNotPrecompiledError
       for an engine asset it didn't declare.

       THE RULE FOR NEW PAGES
         Compose from the tokens and component classes below. A page's own
         <style> block is for genuinely page-specific LAYOUT only (grids,
         scrollspy, the pulse monitor) — never for re-styling a button, chip,
         table, card, badge, or form control. If you reach for an inline color,
         border, or radius, use a token instead.

       TOKENS (:root)
         Color    --bg --panel --ink --muted --line --accent --accent-dark
                  --accent-soft --warn --warn-soft --chip
         Space    --s1 .25 · --s2 .5 · --s3 .75 · --s4 1 · --s5 1.5 · --s6 2 rem
         Radius   --r-sm 6 · --r 10 · --r-pill 999 px
         Type     --fs-xs .75 · --fs-sm .82 · --fs-base .9 · --fs-lg 1.08 ·
                  --fs-display 1.7 rem
         Font     --font-display ui-serif/Georgia (scholarly serif — headings ONLY)
         Depth    --shadow (hairline lift, on cards) · --shadow-pop (popover, defined
                  for later use)

       TYPOGRAPHIC REGISTER
         Headings (h1, h2, .section-head) are set in --font-display — a system
         serif, for a federal-library / scholarly voice at zero dependency cost.
         Everything else — body, nav, chips, eyebrows, buttons, the stat numerals —
         stays the system sans. Don't apply the serif to UI chrome.

       COMPONENTS (defined once, here)
         .card / .panel        bordered surface (hairline + quiet --shadow); .row wraps into columns
         .section-head (h2)    serif section heading; <small> inside = quiet subtitle
         table                 quiet catalog table (th muted, hairline rows)
         .chip                 neutral pill; .chip.tier = accent; .chip.warn = alert
         .badge-live           the "curator-approved, live" accent badge
         .btn                  base button; modifiers:
                                 .btn-affirmative (approve/confirm — accent outline)
                                 .btn-primary     (filled accent — the main action)
                                 .btn-destructive (reject — warn)
                                 .btn-sm          (compact)
         .field                input / select / textarea (shared form control)
         .strip                summary/metric strip (a .card laid out as a chip row)
         .stats-strip          the live-stats panel (eyebrow + numeral grid + facet
                                 chips + footer) — promoted from About so any surface
                                 can report "this collection, right now"
         .muted .samples .mono .warn .big   typographic utilities

       REFERENCE DESK (v0.29)
         The enl-* widget / trace / citation system lives at the BOTTOM of this
         block (chat tool-widgets, the working-trace timeline, inline citations).
         Composed from the tokens; enl-*-scoped so it selects nothing off the chat
         surface even though it ships on every page.

       Page-specific styles still in their views (by design): About (TOC +
       prose grid), Chat (.thread/.bubble/.prompts/.ask — also JS hooks),
       Heartbeat (.pulse-* monitor — also JS hooks).
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
    :root {
      --bg: #f7f7f5; --panel: #fff; --ink: #1c1c1a; --muted: #6b6b66;
      --line: #e3e3df; --accent: #2d6a4f; --accent-dark: #245741; --accent-soft: #e8f0ec;
      --warn: #b4231f; --warn-soft: #fdeceb; --chip: #eef0f2;
      /* spacing scale (8px rhythm, expressed in rem) */
      --s1: .25rem; --s2: .5rem; --s3: .75rem; --s4: 1rem; --s5: 1.5rem; --s6: 2rem;
      /* radii */
      --r-sm: 6px; --r: 10px; --r-pill: 999px;
      /* type scale — sans body, serif headings (--fs-display is h1) */
      --fs-xs: .75rem; --fs-sm: .82rem; --fs-base: .9rem; --fs-lg: 1.08rem;
      --fs-display: 1.7rem;
      /* fonts — body stays system sans; headings take a system serif for a
         scholarly register at zero dependency cost (no web font) */
      --font-display: ui-serif, Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      /* depth — hairline borders stay primary; shadows are a quiet lift only */
      --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, .04);
      --shadow-pop: 0 6px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, .12);
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { margin: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--ink);
      font: 15px/1.5 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif; }
    a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; transition: color .15s; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* ── Navigation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    nav.enl { display: flex; gap: var(--s5); align-items: baseline;
      padding: .8rem 1.25rem; background: var(--panel); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    nav.enl .brand { font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .02em; }
    /* brand → scope selector → scoped destinations. The hairline separator
       after the scope group signals "everything past here is viewed through it". */
    nav.enl .nav-scope { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--s3); }
    /* only fence the scope group off when a switcher is actually present */
    nav.enl .nav-scope.has-scope { padding-right: var(--s5); border-right: 1px solid var(--line); }
    /* the context switcher — styled via the group class, NOT via the element id, so
       the id literal appears in the response ONLY when the element renders (the
       flat-install spec greps the whole body for its absence). The id stays on the
       element itself for the JS onchange hook. */
    nav.enl .nav-scope select { font: inherit; font-size: var(--fs-sm); padding: .15rem .4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r-sm); background: var(--panel);
      color: var(--accent); max-width: 14rem; }
    nav.enl .nav-spacer { margin-left: auto; }
    /* destination links: quiet by default, accent on hover; the current surface
       (marked aria-current="page") sits in accent with a hairline underline. The
       selector is ready even where a surface doesn't yet mark itself. */
    nav.enl a { color: var(--ink); padding-bottom: .1rem; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; }
    nav.enl a:hover { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
    nav.enl a[aria-current="page"] { color: var(--accent); border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }

    /* ── Page frame & headings ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    main.enl { max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 4rem; }
    /* Headings carry the scholarly serif; the rest of the UI stays system sans.
       Generous, deliberate hierarchy so serif reads well on a projector/screen. */
    h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-display);
      font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -.01em; margin: .2rem 0 1.1rem; }
    h2, .section-head { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-lg);
      font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3; margin: 1.8rem 0 .65rem; }
    /* a quiet subtitle that rides alongside a heading — stays sans, regular weight */
    h2 small, .section-head small, .subtitle {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400; font-size: .95rem; color: var(--muted); }

    /* ── Card / panel ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    /* hairline border stays primary; --shadow is a quiet lift off the page */
    .card, .panel { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--r); padding: 1rem 1.1rem; margin: .75rem 0;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
    .row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--s3); }
    .row .card { flex: 1 1 280px; }

    /* ── Chips & badges ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .chip { display: inline-block; background: var(--chip); border-radius: var(--r-pill);
      padding: .1rem .55rem; font-size: .8rem; color: var(--muted); }
    .chip.tier { background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); }
    .chip.warn { background: var(--warn-soft); color: var(--warn); }
    /* the "curator-approved; live but not codified" badge — was repeated inline */
    .badge-live { display: inline-block; background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent);
      border-radius: var(--r-pill); padding: .1rem .55rem; font-size: .8rem; }

    /* ── Typographic utilities ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    .samples { color: var(--muted); font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .big { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 700; }
    code, .mono { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; font-size: .85em; }
    .warn { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 600; }

    /* ── Tables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: .9rem; }
    th, td { text-align: left; padding: .35rem .5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      vertical-align: top; }
    th { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; }
    tr.warn-row td { background: var(--warn-soft); }

    /* ── Summary / metric strip ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .strip { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--s2) var(--s3); }

    /* ── Buttons ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .btn { font: inherit; font-size: var(--fs-base); padding: .35rem .85rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r-sm); background: var(--panel);
      color: var(--ink); cursor: pointer; line-height: 1.3; transition: background .15s, border-color .15s; }
    .btn:hover { background: var(--chip); }
    .btn:disabled { opacity: .55; cursor: default; }
    .btn-sm { font-size: .8rem; padding: .25rem .6rem; }
    .btn-affirmative { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent-soft); background: var(--accent-soft); }
    .btn-affirmative:hover { background: #dde9e2; border-color: var(--accent); }
    .btn-primary { color: #fff; background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--accent-dark); }
    .btn-destructive { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--line); background: var(--panel); }
    .btn-destructive:hover { background: var(--warn-soft); border-color: var(--warn); }

    /* ── Form controls ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .field { font: inherit; font-size: var(--fs-base); padding: .35rem .55rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r-sm); background: var(--panel);
      color: var(--ink); transition: border-color .15s, box-shadow .15s; }
    /* one consistent focus ring across every interactive surface */
    .field:focus,
    .btn:focus-visible,
    nav.enl a:focus-visible,
    nav.enl .nav-scope select:focus-visible,
    button.prompt:focus-visible,
    .ask textarea:focus-visible,
    .ask button:focus-visible {
      outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 1px; }

    /* ── Flash messages ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .flash { padding: .55rem .8rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0 0 1rem; font-size: .9rem; }
    .flash-notice { background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); }
    .flash-alert { background: var(--warn-soft); color: var(--warn); }

    /* ── Requests verdict action group (page-specific layout for suggestions) ─ */
    .verdict { display: flex; gap: var(--s2); align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .verdict form { display: inline-flex; margin: 0; gap: var(--s1); align-items: center; }

    /* chat */
    .thread { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
    .bubble { padding: .6rem .85rem; border-radius: 10px; max-width: 80%; }
    .bubble.user { align-self: flex-end; background: var(--accent-soft); white-space: pre-wrap; }
    .bubble.assistant { align-self: flex-start; background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); }
    /* rendered markdown inside an assistant bubble */
    .bubble.assistant .md > :first-child { margin-top: 0; }
    .bubble.assistant .md > :last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .bubble.assistant .md p { margin: .45rem 0; }
    .bubble.assistant .md h2, .bubble.assistant .md h3, .bubble.assistant .md h4 { margin: .7rem 0 .3rem; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3; }
    .bubble.assistant .md ul, .bubble.assistant .md ol { margin: .35rem 0 .35rem 1.25rem; padding: 0; }
    .bubble.assistant .md li { margin: .15rem 0; }
    .bubble.assistant .md code { background: var(--chip); padding: .05rem .3rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: .9em; }
    .bubble.assistant .md a { word-break: break-word; }
    /* v0.29: the renderer now emits blockquotes, rules, tables, and nested lists.
       Styled from the tokens; a lighter relative of the .enl-quote treatment. */
    .bubble.assistant .md blockquote { margin: .5rem 0; padding: .15rem .75rem;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-soft); color: var(--muted); }
    .bubble.assistant .md hr { border: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); margin: .75rem 0; }
    /* a nested list sits inside its parent <li>: drop the top/bottom gap so it
       hugs the item, keep only the indent. */
    .bubble.assistant .md li > ul, .bubble.assistant .md li > ol { margin: .1rem 0 .1rem 1rem; }
    .bubble.assistant .md table { margin: .5rem 0; font-size: .88rem; }
    .bubble.assistant .md th, .bubble.assistant .md td { padding: .3rem .5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
    .bubble.assistant .md th { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; }
    .provenance { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .35rem; margin-top: .4rem; }
    .prompts { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .4rem; margin: 1rem 0 0; }
    .prompts .label { width: 100%; font-size: .8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: .1rem; }
    button.prompt { cursor: pointer; font: inherit; font-size: .85rem; color: var(--accent);
      background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px; padding: .35rem .75rem;
      transition: background .15s, border-color .15s; }
    button.prompt:hover { background: var(--accent-soft); border-color: var(--accent-soft); }
    .ask { display: flex; gap: .5rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .ask textarea { flex: 1; padding: .6rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px;
      font: inherit; resize: vertical; min-height: 2.6rem; }
    .ask button { padding: 0 1.1rem; border: 0; border-radius: 8px; background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: background .15s; }
    .ask button:hover:not(:disabled) { background: var(--accent-dark); }
    .ask button:disabled { opacity: .5; cursor: default; }

    /* ── Promoted: live-stats strip (shared component, moved from About) ─────
       "this collection, right now" — an eyebrow, a numeral grid, facet chips,
       a footer. Set on accent-soft; numerals stay sans + tabular. Tokens only;
       the former literal rgba(45,106,79,…) tints are now accent-soft / chip. */
    .stats-strip { background: var(--accent-soft); border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--r); padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem 1rem; margin: 0 0 .5rem;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
    .stats-strip .stats-eyebrow { font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .09em;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: .85rem; }
    .stats-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: .35rem 1rem;
      margin-bottom: .15rem; }
    .stats-grid .stat-cell { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .15rem; }
    .stats-grid .stat-cell .stat-num { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent);
      line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -.03em; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .stats-grid .stat-cell .stat-label { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.3; font-weight: 500; }
    .stats-facets { margin-top: .75rem; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: .3rem; }
    .stats-facets .facets-label { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-right: .1rem; }
    .stats-facets .facet-chip { display: inline-block; background: var(--chip); color: var(--accent);
      border-radius: var(--r-pill); padding: .1rem .55rem; font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.5; }
    .stats-footer { margin-top: .75rem; font-size: var(--fs-sm); color: var(--muted);
      padding-top: .6rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); line-height: 1.5; }
    .stats-footer strong { color: var(--ink); }
    @media (max-width: 759px) {
      .stats-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: .75rem .75rem; }
    }

    /* ── Reduced motion ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Honor the OS setting: drop the hover/focus color fades on every
       interactive surface that carries a transition. (The fades are color-only
       and low-risk, but the preference is a deliverable, so respect it.) */
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      a, .field, .btn, button.prompt, .ask button { transition: none; }
    }

    /* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       REFERENCE DESK — enl-* widget / trace / citation system (v0.29)
       ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       The chat tool-widgets, the working-trace timeline, and the inline citation
       affordances. Composed entirely from the :root tokens above. Every selector
       is enl-*-scoped (or the shared stat-strip / .enl-accuracy / .facet-chip
       classes defined earlier) so this block selects NOTHING outside the chat
       surface — it renders on every page (shared layout) but is inert with
       federation off. Widget HTML is emitted by app/services/enliterator/chat/
       widget.rb; the trace/citation/sources/typing/handoff classes are targets
       for the later client-JS (no server renderer emits them yet).
       Only literal allowed: #fff (white-on-accent text). Everything else: tokens.
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

    /* ── Reference Desk: working trace (client-JS target) ──────────────────── */
    .enl-trace { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r); background: var(--bg); margin: 0 0 var(--s3); overflow: hidden; }
    .enl-trace__head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--s2); padding: var(--s2) var(--s3); font-size: var(--fs-sm); color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; cursor: default; }
    .enl-trace[data-state="done"] .enl-trace__head { cursor: pointer; }
    .enl-trace[data-state="done"] .enl-trace__steps { display: none; }
    .enl-trace[data-state="done"].is-open .enl-trace__steps { display: block; }
    .enl-trace__steps { padding: 0 var(--s3) var(--s2); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--s1); }
    /* NOTE: trace steps are .enl-trace__step (NOT .enl-step — that belongs to the trajectory widget, below) */
    .enl-trace__step { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: flex-start; gap: var(--s2); font-size: var(--fs-sm); color: var(--ink); padding: var(--s1) 0; }
    .enl-trace__step .enl-trace__dot { flex: none; width: 14px; height: 14px; margin-top: 2px; border-radius: var(--r-pill); border: 2px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-trace__step--working .enl-trace__dot { border-color: var(--accent); border-top-color: transparent; animation: enl-spin .8s linear infinite; }
    .enl-trace__step--done .enl-trace__dot { border-color: var(--accent); background: var(--accent); position: relative; }
    .enl-trace__step--done .enl-trace__dot::after { content: "✓"; position: absolute; inset: 0; color: #fff; font-size: 9px; line-height: 10px; text-align: center; }
    .enl-trace__step--error .enl-trace__dot { border-color: var(--warn); background: var(--warn); }
    .enl-trace__label { flex: 1; min-width: 60%; }
    .enl-trace__label .desk { color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-trace__step > details { flex-basis: 100%; margin-top: var(--s1); }
    .enl-trace__step > details > summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); list-style: none; }
    .enl-handoff { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--s2); font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--accent); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; font-weight: 700; margin: var(--s2) 0; }
    .enl-handoff::before, .enl-handoff::after { content: ""; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--accent-soft); }
    .enl-typing { display: inline-flex; gap: 4px; }
    .enl-typing span { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: var(--r-pill); background: var(--muted); opacity: .4; }
    /* Input polish (client-JS targets; the federation JS adds these classes — with
       federation off no element ever carries them, so .ask textarea / .ask button
       render exactly as before). The textarea is grown by JS up to --enl-ta-max,
       then scrolls; the auto-height needs the JS, so the class only disables the
       manual resize handle it would fight with. */
    .ask textarea.enl-autosize { resize: none; overflow-y: auto; max-height: var(--enl-ta-max, 12rem); }
    .ask button.enl-send--working { position: relative; }

    /* ── Widget chassis + structured variants ──────────────────────────────── */
    .enl-widget { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r); background: var(--panel); padding: var(--s3); margin: var(--s2) 0; font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-widget__head { font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: var(--s2); }
    .enl-widget__json { background: var(--bg); border-radius: var(--r-sm); padding: var(--s2); margin: 0; max-height: 16rem; overflow: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: var(--fs-xs); }
    .enl-widget__facet { margin: 0 0 var(--s2); }
    .enl-widget__facet-name { font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); text-transform: capitalize; margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-claim { padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); line-height: 1.45; }
    .enl-claim:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .enl-claim__key { color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-claim__value { color: var(--ink); }
    .enl-claim__conf, .enl-claim__verdict { display: inline-block; margin-left: var(--s1); font-size: var(--fs-xs); padding: 0 .4rem; border-radius: var(--r-pill); background: var(--chip); color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-claim__verdict { background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); }
    .enl-prov__claim { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-prov__visit { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: var(--s2); }
    .enl-prov__audits { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .enl-prov__audit { padding: var(--s1) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); line-height: 1.45; }
    .enl-accuracy__anchor { margin-top: var(--s2); font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--accent); }
    /* trajectory: render_trajectory emits .enl-step / __at / __tier / __ops (NOT .enl-trace__step) */
    .enl-traj { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .enl-traj .enl-step { padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); line-height: 1.45; }
    .enl-traj .enl-step:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .enl-step__at { font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace; color: var(--muted); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }
    .enl-step__tier { display: inline-block; background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); border-radius: var(--r-pill); padding: 0 .45rem; font-size: var(--fs-xs); margin: 0 var(--s1); }
    .enl-step__ops { color: var(--ink); }
    .enl-results { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .enl-result { padding: var(--s2) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-result:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .enl-result__label { font-weight: 600; }
    .enl-result__type { display: inline-block; margin-left: var(--s1); font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); background: var(--chip); border-radius: var(--r-pill); padding: 0 .45rem; }
    .enl-result__excerpt { color: var(--muted); margin: var(--s1) 0; line-height: 1.45; }
    .enl-result__counts { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-quote { margin: 0; padding: var(--s2) var(--s3); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); background: var(--accent-soft); border-radius: 0 var(--r-sm) var(--r-sm) 0; font-style: italic; line-height: 1.5; }
    .enl-widget--quote-unlocated .enl-quote { border-left-color: var(--muted); background: var(--bg); font-style: normal; }
    .enl-quote__flag { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--warn); margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-edges { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 var(--s2); padding: 0; }
    .enl-edge { padding: var(--s1) 0; }
    .enl-edge__key { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .enl-edge__degraded { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--warn); background: var(--warn-soft); border-radius: var(--r-sm); padding: var(--s1) var(--s2); }
    .enl-neighbor { padding: var(--s1) 0; color: var(--ink); }
    /* overview: render_collection_overview wraps the context tree + accuracy table in collapsed details */
    .enl-overview__contexts, .enl-overview__accuracy { margin-top: var(--s2); }
    .enl-overview__contexts > summary, .enl-overview__accuracy > summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 600; }

    /* ── Raw-tool cards (browse_subjects / vocabulary / recent_activity) ───── */
    /* browse_subjects: per-heading block → key (+ approximate note) → term/count chips → "show all" */
    .enl-headings__empty { color: var(--muted); font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-headings__heading { padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-headings__heading:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .enl-headings__key { font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent); margin: var(--s2) 0 var(--s1); text-transform: capitalize; }
    .enl-headings__vals { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--s1); }
    .enl-headval { background: var(--chip); border-radius: var(--r-pill); padding: .1rem .55rem; font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--ink); }
    .enl-headval b { color: var(--accent); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; margin-left: .25rem; }
    .enl-headings__approx { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-top: var(--s1); }
    .enl-headings__more { margin-top: var(--s1); }
    .enl-headings__more > summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }
    /* vocabulary: per facet → name + tier chip + scheduled marker (the .enl-vocab__head row), then term rows */
    .enl-vocab__facet { padding: var(--s2) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-vocab__facet:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .enl-vocab__head { margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-vocab__name { font-weight: 600; text-transform: capitalize; margin-right: var(--s1); }
    .enl-vocab__sched { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-left: var(--s1); }
    .enl-vocab__term { display: block; font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); padding: var(--s1) 0 0; }
    .enl-vocab__term--req::before { content: "• "; color: var(--accent); }
    /* recent_activity: the headline lead line, then visits-by-tier + failures behind collapsed details */
    .enl-activity__headline { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-activity__empty { color: var(--muted); font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-activity__visits, .enl-activity__failures { margin-top: var(--s2); }
    .enl-activity__visits > summary, .enl-activity__failures > summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 600; }
    .enl-activity__tiers, .enl-activity__failure-list { list-style: none; margin: var(--s1) 0 0; padding: 0; }
    .enl-activity__tier { padding: var(--s1) 0; font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-activity__tier b { color: var(--accent); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; margin-left: var(--s1); }
    .enl-activity__failure { padding: var(--s1) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-activity__where { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-activity__error { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--warn); font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, monospace; }
    .enl-activity__truncated { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-top: var(--s1); }

    /* ── Citations (client-JS target) ──────────────────────────────────────── */
    .enl-cite { font: inherit; vertical-align: super; font-size: .7em; line-height: 0; min-width: 16px; height: 16px; padding: 0 4px; margin: 0 1px; border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft); border-radius: var(--r-pill); background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); cursor: pointer; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .enl-cite:hover, .enl-cite:focus-visible { background: var(--accent); color: #fff; outline: none; }
    /* v0.32: a navigable phrase in the answer — click populates the composer with a
       follow-up question (distinct from the superscript cite, which opens the record). */
    .enl-ask { cursor: pointer; color: inherit; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--accent); border-radius: 2px; }
    .enl-ask:hover, .enl-ask:focus-visible { background: var(--accent-soft); outline: none; }
    .enl-cite__pop { position: absolute; z-index: 20; max-width: 22rem; background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--r); box-shadow: var(--shadow-pop); padding: var(--s3); font-size: var(--fs-sm); line-height: 1.45; }
    .enl-cite__pop .label { font-weight: 600; display: block; margin-bottom: var(--s1); }
    .enl-cite__pop .type { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); }
    .enl-sources { margin-top: var(--s4); padding-top: var(--s3); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .enl-sources__head { font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
    .enl-sources__head:hover, .enl-sources__head:focus-visible { color: var(--text); outline: none; }
    .enl-sources__disclosure[open] > .enl-sources__head { margin-bottom: var(--s2); }
    .enl-sources__item { display: flex; gap: var(--s2); padding: var(--s1) 0; font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-sources__num { flex: none; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
    .enl-chat-error { background: var(--warn-soft); color: var(--warn); border-radius: var(--r-sm); padding: var(--s2) var(--s3); font-size: var(--fs-sm); margin: var(--s2) 0; }

    /* ── Actionable error card (v0.30, client-JS target) ─────────────────────
       A structured alert: the headline always, then (dev/detail-on only) the
       exception detail, where it happened, and an actionable hint. Like an
       alert — a warn-tinted card; the hint is highlighted as the line to act on. */
    .enl-error { background: var(--warn-soft); border: 1px solid var(--warn); border-left: 3px solid var(--warn); border-radius: var(--r-sm); padding: var(--s3); margin: var(--s2) 0; }
    .enl-error__msg { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 600; font-size: var(--fs-sm); }
    .enl-error__detail { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-top: var(--s2); white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; }
    .enl-error__where { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--muted); margin-top: var(--s1); }
    .enl-error__hint { font-size: var(--fs-sm); color: var(--accent); background: var(--accent-soft); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); border-radius: 0 var(--r-sm) var(--r-sm) 0; padding: var(--s2) var(--s3); margin-top: var(--s3); }

    /* ── Motion ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    @keyframes enl-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
    @keyframes enl-blink { 0%,100% { opacity: .3; } 50% { opacity: 1; } }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
      .enl-typing span { animation: enl-blink 1.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      .enl-typing span:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: .2s; }
      .enl-typing span:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: .4s; }
    }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .enl-trace__step--working .enl-trace__dot { animation: none; border-top-color: var(--accent); }
      .enl-typing span { opacity: .6; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="enl">
    <%# brand → scope → the scoped destinations. The context switcher scopes the
        content of every surface that follows it, so it sits with the brand,
        fenced off by a hairline separator (the .nav-scope group). Flat installs
        with no tree seeded show only the brand — byte-identical to before. %>
    <div class="nav-scope<%= " has-scope" if context_switcher_options.any? %>">
      <span class="brand">Enliterator</span>
      <% if context_switcher_options.any? %>
        <select id="ctx-switch" title="View through a context"
                onchange="location.search='?context='+encodeURIComponent(this.value)">
          <option value="root" <%= "selected" unless current_context %>>whole collection</option>
          <% context_switcher_options.each do |label, key| %>
            <option value="<%= key %>" <%= "selected" if current_context&.key == key %>><%= label %></option>
          <% end %>
        </select>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <%= link_to "Status", root_path %>
    <%= link_to "Catalog", catalog_path %>
    <%= link_to "Chat", conversation_path %>
    <%= link_to "Requests", suggestions_path %>
    <%= link_to "Review", review_path %>
    <%= link_to "Contexts", contexts_path %>
    <%= link_to "Atlas", atlas_path %>
    <%= link_to "Heartbeat", heartbeat_path %>
    <% if Enliterator.configuration.chat_persona_editing %><%= link_to "Desks", desks_path %><% end %>
    <%= link_to "Settings", settings_path, class: "nav-spacer" %>
    <%= link_to "About", about_path %>
  </nav>
  <main class="enl">
    <% flash.each do |type, msg| %>
      <div class="flash flash-<%= type %>"><%= msg %></div>
    <% end %>
    <%= yield %>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
